          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brown and braise",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the {{vegetable-oil}} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Brown the {{sausages-pork}} all over, about 5 minutes. Remove and set aside. In the same pan, cook the {{onion}} and {{pepper-red}} over medium heat for 8 minutes until softened. Add the {{garlic}} and {{paprika-sweet}} and cook for 1 minute. Add the {{tomato-puree}} and stir for 1 minute. Add the {{tinned-tomatoes}} and {{bay-leaves}}. Season with {{sea-salt-fine}} and {{black-pepper}}. Return the sausages to the pan. Simmer uncovered for 25 minutes, turning the sausages once, until the sauce has thickened and the sausages are cooked through. Remove the bay leaves. Serve with mashed potato or rice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Simmer uncovered for the full 25 minutes. Tinned tomatoes vary in water content, if still thin, continue simmering for another 10 minutes",
              "cause": "Too much liquid added, or not simmered long enough uncovered",
              "symptom": "Watery sauce that does not thicken"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Brown at medium-high heat, not full heat. Once in the sauce the sausages should simmer gently, not boil",
              "cause": "Initial browning at too high a heat",
              "symptom": "Sausages split during braising"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sausage casserole is a winter weeknight supper that works equally for children and adults. It is the kind of dish that can be started when you get home and is ready in under an hour. The sauce improves overnight, making it a good candidate for batch cooking.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
